# Heading and hero text partition

When writing multi-line headings (e.g. hero titles, section headings), control line breaks so that:

1. **Phrases stay together** – Don’t split a natural phrase across lines (e.g. keep “engaging courses” together, or “in minutes”).
2. **Avoid single words on a line** – Prefer breaking so the second line has at least two words unless the design explicitly wants one word per line.
3. **Use explicit breaks** – Use `<br />` or separate `<span className="block">` elements so the partition is stable across viewports.

## Examples

```tsx
// ❌ BAD – “courses” alone on a line, “in” can wrap awkwardly
<span className="block">Create engaging</span>
<span className="block">courses in minutes</span>

// ❌ BAD – phrase split
<span className="block">Create engaging courses</span>
<span className="block">in minutes</span>
// (can wrap to “Create engaging” / “courses” on small screens)

// ✅ GOOD – clear three-line partition
<span className="block">Create engaging</span>
<span className="block">courses</span>
<span className="block">in <span className="gradient...">minutes</span></span>
```

For login-style headings (e.g. “Instantly create and sell engaging courses”):

- Prefer: **“Instantly create and sell”** / **“engaging courses”** so “engaging courses” stays together.
- Avoid: “Instantly create and sell engaging” / “courses” (single word on second line).
